 Die unverbrauchte Perspektive macht den Band zur inspirierenden Lektüre – nicht nur für Studienanfänger der Architektur, sondern für alle, die wissen möchten, um was es in der Architektur eigentlich geht – und ging.  aThis history-by-theory and theory-by-history book helps its reader make sense of the chaotic multitude of world architecture through time. In contrast to other history books this book is brief but to the point, perceiving architecture as part of human civilisation. Its’ focus on issues such as: “is concept and form or matter the most important ‘component’ of architecture?”, “how close is architecture to spectacle?”, “is less really more?” makes it a good reading for both freshmen students of architecture and the reader who wants to get a grasp of what architecture is–and has been–really about.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aArchitecturexHistory. 4aArchitektur. 4aArchitekturgeschichte. 4aGeschichtstheorie. 4aVielfalt in der Architektur. 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh  aArchitektur.  aArchitekturgeschichte.  aGeschichtstheorie.  aVielfalt in der Architektur.0 cEPUBz97838685989570 cprintz978386859315040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978386859894040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783868598940423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783868598940.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_AD  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK